# Student Resource Sharing Platform

## Project Overview

The Student Resource Sharing Platform is a web-based application developed to help students share, upload, explore, save, and manage study materials in one place. The main purpose of this project is to provide an easy and organized platform where students can access useful academic resources such as notes, documents, PDFs, assignments, and other learning materials.

This project contains a frontend for students and administrators, and a backend system to manage data, authentication, uploaded resources, and admin operations.

---

## Project Goal

The goal of this project is to create a simple and user-friendly study material sharing system where:

- Students can sign up and sign in.
- Students can upload study materials.
- Students can explore available materials.
- Students can save useful materials.
- Students can view their uploaded materials.
- Admin can manage users and uploaded resources.
- The system can store and retrieve data using a database.

---

## Technologies Used

### Frontend

- React.js
- Vite
- JavaScript
- CSS

### Backend

- FastAPI
- Python
- MongoDB

### Version Control

- Git
- GitHub

